# Line-ending policy for this repository.
#
# The codebase is authored on Windows (PowerShell 5.1) but is git-tracked and
# mostly stored as plain LF today -- PowerShell 5.1 and Excel COM do not
# require CRLF in .ps1/.psd1 source files, only in the multi-line strings
# they emit at runtime. Declaring `text eol=lf` here keeps every checkout
# (Windows office PC or this Linux dev environment) normalized to LF and
# stops editor/OS line-ending churn from drowning real diffs in noise -- see
# CHANGELOG.md's 2026-07-21 entry, where a single CRLF whole-file rewrite of
# a 31-line change showed up as 2700+ inserted/deleted lines.
*.ps1  text eol=lf
*.psd1 text eol=lf
*.psm1 text eol=lf
*.md   text eol=lf
*.json text eol=lf
*.yml  text eol=lf
*.txt  text eol=lf
.gitattributes text eol=lf
.gitignore     text eol=lf
